snippet.title: Gus Goes to Cyberopolis (1994) | 4K/60
snippet.description:
Meet the hippest hound around!

Gus Goes to Cyberopolis is a CD-ROM children's edutainment title for Pippin consoles in which young users can explore numerous environments, seeking out the Cyberbuds. Parents can set the difficulty for children ages 3 to 8, Gus Goes to Cyberopolis was originally released in 1994 for Macintosh and Windows 3.1 by Modern Media Ventures as a follow-up to 1993's Gus Goes to Cybertown. The Pippin port of Gus Goes to Cyberopolis was distributed by Bandai Digital Entertainment in 1996
